detaileddescription.para:
Helper function for computing the analytical result for the asymptotic tails of the bubble integral in the a and t channel, assuming the self-energy to be decayed to the Hartree value. See the function asymp_corrections_bubble below.
w
: Bosonic transfer frequency
vmin
: Lower limit of the numerically evaluated integral
vmax
: Upper limit of the numerically evaluated integral
Sigma_H
: Hartree self-energy
Delta
: Hybridization (~ flow parameter) at which the bubble is evaluated
eta_1
: +1/-1 if first propagator in the bubble is retarded/advanced
eta_2
: +1/-1 if second propagator in the bubble is retarded/advanced
: Analytical result of the integrated tails
